Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.20,0:01:07.20,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}翻譯：閒著沒事幹的MT 隨便改
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.32,0:01:18.89,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}人類如何瞭解未知\NHow does one come to know The Unknowable?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.09,0:01:21.70,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}人類需要什麼技能\NWhat faculties must a man possess?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.90,0:01:23.86,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}自從人類發現鯨油\NSince it was discovered that whale oil
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.01,0:01:27.16,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}可以以前所未有的方式點亮我們的城市\Ncould light our cities in ways never achieved before,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.36,0:01:29.49,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}全世界需求量暴漲\Nit created global demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.69,0:01:33.31,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}使人類向開始向\NIt had pushed man to venture further and further
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.51,0:01:36.08,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}海洋更深處冒險\Ninto The Deep, Blue Unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.28,0:01:38.59,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們不知道海洋的深度\NWe know not its depths,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.79,0:01:41.49,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}也不瞭解海洋裏的生物\Nnor the host of creatures that live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.69,0:01:45.14,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}怪物是否真的存在\NMonsters, are they real?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.01,0:02:00.08,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}或者這些故事只是讓我們對海洋隱藏的秘密有所敬畏\NOr do the stories exist only to make us respect the sea's dark secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.01,0:02:11.08,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}楠塔基特島 馬薩諸塞州 1850年二月
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.65,0:02:15.81,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}這個問題使我即苦惱又興奮\NThe question both vexes and excites me,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.01,0:02:19.72,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}也是我再次向您寫信請求一次會面的原因\Nand is the reason I've written you a second time to request a meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.82,0:02:21.09,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}一次和您交談的機會 先生\NA conversation with you, Sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.15,0:02:24.51,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我相信這會對我將要寫的小說有很大幫助\NI believe will serve me well for the novel I intend to write,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.71,0:02:27.63,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}小說暫且名為 白鯨記\Ncurrently entitled Moby Dick
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.13,0:02:30.72,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我期望您能考慮我的提議\NI hope you will reconsider my offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.32,0:02:37.78,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}未知 我的想像力始終想冒險的地方\NThe Unknown, that is where my imagination yearns to venture.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.01,0:02:41.20,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}始終折磨我的問題是\NAnd so, the question plagues me still:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.22,0:02:44.92,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}人類如何才能探索未知\NHow does a man come to know The Unknowable?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.76,0:02:48.85,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}此致 赫爾曼·梅爾維爾\NSincerely, Herman Melville.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.67,0:02:51.47,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們打烊了\NWe're closed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.95,0:02:53.98,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}8點後不接客\NNo borders after eight o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.41,0:03:06.01,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你居然來了\NYou came.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.06,0:03:17.47,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}親愛的 有人來看你\NThere's someone here for you, My Love.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.67,0:03:18.67,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}湯姆·尼克森\NTom Nickerson?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.07,0:03:23.47,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}赫爾曼·梅爾維爾\NHerman Melville.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.87,0:03:25.84,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們收到了你的來信\NWe received your letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.82,0:03:30.93,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你要麼走投無路要麼是個傻子大老遠跑來楠塔基特\NYou're either a desperate man or a fool to come all the way to Nantucket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:36.33,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我的提議還在\NWell, my offer still stands.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.53,0:03:39.10,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}3個月的住宿換一晚的交談\NThree months'lodgings for a single night's talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.66,0:03:42.49,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}這是我所有的錢了\NIt's all I have in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.84,0:03:45.19,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}但我更願意看作是一次投資\NBut I'd prefer to think of it as an investment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.36,0:03:48.71,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我想要你告訴我\NI want you to tell me what happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.91,0:03:50.51,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}埃塞克斯號發生了什麼\Nto the Essex.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.99,0:03:59.29,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你覺得發生了什麼\NWell,what do you think happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.49,0:04:02.30,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}有傳言埃塞克斯號\NThere are rumblings,rumors that the Essex...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.45,0:04:05.85,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你想要什麼 期望聽到什麼故事\NWhat do you want?What story do you expect to hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.05,0:04:08.03,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}白鯨的故事\NThat of The Whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.29,0:04:14.18,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}埃塞克斯號擱淺了 有完整的報告\NThe Essex ran aground, there was a full inquiry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.28,0:04:16.80,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我覺得那份報告不是事實全部\NI believe the inquiry was less than truthful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.51,0:04:19.00,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}滾出去\NGet out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.16,0:04:23.68,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}先生 你是埃塞克斯號上唯一的倖存者\NYou are the last survivor or the Essex, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.88,0:04:25.98,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}如果你不說出來 誰還能講出事實\NIf you won't talk, who will?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.08,0:04:30.14,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你沒聽見我的話嗎 出去\NYou do not hear me, leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.82,0:04:37.10,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你不能走 拜託 就一會兒  他沒心情談\N- You mustn't go, please, just take a minute... - He's in no mind to talk, and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.21,0:04:39.57,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我不是大老遠來就是為了被羞辱和浪費時間\NI haven't come all this way to be humiliated and waste my time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.62,0:04:41.39,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}拜託了 梅爾維爾 先生\NPlease, Mr. Melville,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.03,0:04:48.00,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他從來不跟別人談論埃塞克斯號 包括我 從不\Nhe won't talk about the Essex to me, to anyone... never has... never.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.40,0:04:50.97,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我一點都不瞭解他\NI don't know anything about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.17,0:04:58.39,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他的精神在受折磨 需要救贖\NHis soul is... in torment, and in need of confession.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.43,0:05:02.72,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}拜託了 請讓我和他談 拜託了\NPlease, just let me talk to him... please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.59,0:05:10.31,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}親愛的\NLove,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.66,0:05:17.49,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我覺得和這個年輕人談會對你有好處\NI believe it would do you good to talk to the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.28,0:05:19.41,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}不\NNo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.96,0:05:25.01,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你聽著\NYou listen well!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.51,0:05:29.19,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你酗酒要死的時候誰撐著這個家了\NWho holds this place together while you drink yourself to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.75,0:05:33.20,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你必須和這個年輕人談\NYou WILL talk with this man, as much as is necessary...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.51,0:05:35.44,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}才能保住你的錢\Nto keep the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.50,0:05:39.61,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你知道我們的處境 湯姆\NYou know our circumstances, Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.47,0:05:53.39,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我只說必要的\NOnly as much as is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.74,0:06:00.06,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我去拿威士忌\NI'll get whiskey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.76,0:06:09.84,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我忘了在信裏提到我曾經是一名捕鯨手\NI neglected to mention it in my letter, but I was a whaler once.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:14.91,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}有過一次出航 新手\NOne trip. I mean... green hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.98,0:06:17.67,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}那麼你應該都經歷過了\NSo, you've seen it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.20,0:06:21.57,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我妻子讀過你的書\NMy wife read your books.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.77,0:06:26.10,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}她很喜歡 很高興聽到\N- She enjoyed them. - Happy to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.15,0:06:30.54,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}銷量很好 但我估計這個故事\NThey had good sales, but I think that THIS story
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.30,0:06:34.88,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}甚至能超過我銷量不錯的第一部小說\Ncould surpass even the success of my first novel... which did quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:38.82,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}又一個你的航海軼事\NAnother of your seafaring yarns.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.01,0:06:44.88,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你聽說過霍索恩嗎 梅爾維爾先生\NHave you read Hawthorne, Mr. Melville?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:50.03,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}當下有一名作家 一個大作家\NNow, there's a writer, a great writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.19,0:06:51.69,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他是的\NHe is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.06,0:06:57.27,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}但他不在這兒 因為我自己的原因\NBut he is not here, and I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.47,0:07:00.10,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我在這兒\Nfor my own particular reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.74,0:07:12.88,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我會告訴你埃塞克斯號 我相信你會失望的\NI'll tell you of the Essex, I believe you will be disappointed,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.08,0:07:15.88,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}但我說的每個字都是真實的\Nbut every word I say will be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.37,0:07:21.55,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}埃塞克斯號的故事就是兩個男人的故事\NThe story of the Essex is the story of two men...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.06,0:07:24.96,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}喬治·波拉德船長\NCaptain George Pollard,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.62,0:07:29.63,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}和他大副 歐文·查斯\Nand his first mate, Owen Chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.83,0:07:33.09,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}歐文 你不能遲到\NOwen, you don't want to be late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.29,0:07:38.41,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我會到那兒的 再說了 不能讓我們的女兒睡在破陋的房子裏對吧\NI'll be there, besides, can't have our daughter sleeping under a leaky roof, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.61,0:07:40.71,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你為什麼那麼肯定是女兒\NWhat makes you so sure it's a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.91,0:07:45.93,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}肯定是的 她會提醒我你這麼固執為什麼我還是愛你\NWell, it has to be, so she can remind me why I have to love you, and you being stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.13,0:07:48.83,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}如果是女兒她會更像你而不是我\NIf it's to to be a daughter she'll be a version of you, not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.98,0:07:51.46,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}金髮而且一心想征服世界\NBlond locks and determined to conquer the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.35,0:07:55.16,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我想過了今天你會用那件外套換一套制服\NI suppose after today you'll be tradin' in that tunic for a uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.28,0:08:00.62,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}沒錯 終於能離開這破地方去賺個區艾瑟 船長該住的房子了\NThat's right, finally out of this patch of dirt for a captain's house in Quaise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.81,0:08:03.79,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我不想住在周邊都是古板的鄰居的房子裏\NI don't need one of those houses in town with stuffy neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.99,0:08:05.93,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}這裏有足夠供我們一家三口居住的地方\NThere's plenty room here for the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.03,0:08:10.85,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}有時候你的溫情真讓人受不了\NYa know, sometimes your kind heart and good nature is just unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.52,0:08:14.35,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}去做你的船長吧\NGo get your captaincy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.03,0:08:59.64,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}- 你下注 1美元9分\N- What's your bid? - One ninety.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:02.40,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我用2美元買到了一千加侖\NI've got a thousand gallons at two dollars!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.49,0:09:03.88,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我佔40份\NI'll take 40 shares.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.22,0:09:08.14,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}賣家 賣家 在這\NSeller, seller, over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.40,0:09:16.02,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}克雷斯拉回來了1600桶\NCriterion's back with a fine haul, 1600 barrels.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.25,0:09:21.17,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}倫敦市場新紀錄 50磅銀器換燈芯\NA new record, 50 pounds Sterling for headmatter on the London market.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.82,0:09:33.80,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}早上好 查斯先生\NGood morning Mr. Chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.90,0:09:35.82,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}馬森先生 請進\N- Mr. Mason. - Come in, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.33,0:09:40.23,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我的合夥人 本傑明·福勒\NMy partner, Benjamin Fuller.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.43,0:09:42.82,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}早上好 先生 請坐\N- Good morning, Sir. - Do sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.57,0:09:51.34,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}查斯先生 我們希望你知道我們對你\NMr. Chase, I do hope you realize how satisfied we are
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.61,0:09:53.99,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}為我們多年的工作有多麼滿意\Nwith the work you've done for us over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.04,0:09:55.11,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}謝謝 先生\NOh, thank you, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.31,0:09:57.94,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們其中一艘船 埃塞克斯號\NAnd one of our ships, the Essex
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.14,0:10:02.19,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}已經花大價錢修整好準備出海了\Nhas just be refitted at great expense and is to go to sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.84,0:10:04.94,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}因為在她身上花了大價錢\NNow, having made such an investment in her,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.02,0:10:08.42,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們希望確保她在最適合的人手裏\Nwe want to be sure she's in the best possible hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.67,0:10:10.47,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}所以\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.58,0:10:14.20,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們很高興邀請你成為這艘船的\Nit gives us great pleasure to offer you a position aboard her...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.04,0:10:16.64,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}大副\Nas first mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.88,0:10:21.79,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}大副 是的\N- As first mate? - Uh-hum.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.30,0:10:26.10,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}馬森先生 你許諾過我上次出航帶回來1500桶的話\NMr. Mason, you... you promised me command of a ship after my last voyage when
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.20,0:10:30.89,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}會讓我當一艘船的船長 你保證過的\NI brought you back 1500 barrels, do you remember? You gave me your word.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.09,0:10:33.67,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}那個承諾要推遲了\NThat promise must now be deferred.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.87,0:10:37.14,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}像別人一樣我們最近行情不好\NLike everyone else we've had a mean time recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.22,0:10:38.66,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我看不是\NWell, never on my watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.76,0:10:43.60,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}楠塔基特主宰了全球市場 這點不能變\NNantucket now dominates the world market, that must not change.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.80,0:10:46.75,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}沒有時間來試驗\NThis is no time for experimentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.95,0:10:50.40,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}埃塞克斯號必須由喬治·波拉德指揮\NThe Essex will be captained by George Pollard,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.41,0:10:53.49,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}偉大的捕鯨家族的後裔\Nscion of a great whaling family.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.97,0:10:57.33,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他的父親也是我們的老主顧\NHis father also happens to be our patron.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.53,0:11:01.72,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}血統 查斯先生 你可以有出色的航海技能\NBlood, Mr. Chase, you can have all the voyages under your belt you want
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.92,0:11:03.77,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}但血統還是更重要\Nbut blood will always win out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.87,0:11:06.73,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}但是血統不會幫你的船裝滿油回來 馬森先生\NYes, well, blood's not gonna fill the ship with oil, Mr. Mason.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.84,0:11:10.63,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}要成功指揮船 船長需要被人尊重 如果別人不尊重他怎麼辦\NTo successfully command, a captain needs respect, now, what if the men don't respect him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.13,0:11:13.28,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你就要確保別人尊重他\NYou will make sure that they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.48,0:11:15.25,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}再見 先生們\NGood day, Gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.35,0:11:17.90,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我理解你的失落\NI understand your disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.95,0:11:18.95,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}所以\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.64,0:11:22.09,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}115金幣\NA one-fifteenth lay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.99,0:11:26.93,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我從來沒有給新長官支付過這麼多\NAnd that's more than I've ever paid any first officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.03,0:11:31.67,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}如果你帶回來2000桶油 我向你保證\NAnd if you bring back 2000 barrels of oil, I'll give you my word,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.97,0:11:35.39,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}下次你就會是船長\Nnext time you WILL have your captaincy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.59,0:11:38.45,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你之前給過我保證來 馬森先生\NYou've given me your word before, Mr. Mason.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.48,0:11:43.04,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}這次我需要書面保證\NSo, this time I'll take it in writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.01,0:12:01.52,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}波拉德船長 我們和查斯先生達成了協議\NCaptain Pollard, we've just had a most agreeable conversation with Mr. Chase,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.72,0:12:03.75,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他會很榮幸服務於您\Nwho'd be honored to serve under you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.31,0:12:07.35,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我很高興聽到\NI'm glad to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.55,0:12:09.88,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}現在我得照顧個沒經驗的\NNow I'm to babysit a greenhorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.08,0:12:14.23,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}一個含著他媽的金勺長大的船長了\NSome cheerless Nantucket born with a damned silver spoon in his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.43,0:12:16.08,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我真應該當面拒絕\NI should have thrown their offer back in their faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.15,0:12:20.05,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}為什麼 你已經拿到書面承諾了\NWhy? You now have the offer of command in writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.15,0:12:23.61,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}騙子的世界什麼都是假的 即使是書面承諾\NYes, well, a liar's word is worthless, even ON paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.49,0:12:36.83,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你知道即使你是商人我還是會愛上你的\NYou know I'd love you just as much if you were a merchant captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.03,0:12:38.86,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你不能離開兩年之久\NAnd you wouldn't be gone for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.06,0:12:40.44,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我不會離開兩年之久的\NI won't be gone two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.49,0:12:43.52,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}貝德福德家的捕鯨人上周回來了 離開了有三年\NA Bedford whaler came back last week was gone three.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.18,0:12:46.76,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}她失去了兩個男人 而且驚魂落魄\NShe lost two men and still with her hull half empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.85,0:12:49.64,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他們是貝德福德家 沒有我在\NWell, they were from Bedford and they didn't have me aboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.29,0:12:56.33,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}婊子養的\NSon of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.73,0:13:01.28,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我要指揮我自己的船\NI will captain my own ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.36,0:13:03.90,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}一艘捕鯨船\Na whaling ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.81,0:13:07.13,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}靠他們我們只能永遠在這個鬼地方\NUp to them all we'd ever have is a patch of dirt
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.20,0:13:08.55,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我不會讓這發生的 佩吉\Nand that's not going to happen, Peggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.68,0:13:11.00,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你父親也是這麼說的 你不能這麼說\NThose'd be your father's words, not yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.09,0:13:12.64,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他的話怎麼了\NWhat's wrong with his words?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.48,0:13:16.34,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他想要為家人為自己爭取\NHe wanted things for his family, for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.03,0:13:19.77,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他是個夢想家 歐文 是的 他是\N- He was a dreamer, Owen - Yes, he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.14,0:13:23.69,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}夢想大海 不帶那些廢物們出海\NDreamed of the sea and never got to sea with men like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.73,0:13:25.94,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}至少他看到了他的孩子出生\NAt least he got to see his children born.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.30,0:13:36.62,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我只能幹這些\NIt's all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.05,0:13:42.06,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}對不起\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.17,0:13:45.97,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我嫁給了一個捕鯨人\NI married a whaleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.48,0:13:59.34,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我會盡快回來 我發誓\NI'll come back as quick as the sun is night, I swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.38,0:14:13.73,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}一定要回來 向我保證\NPlease come back... promise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.96,0:14:18.85,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我已經向你發誓了 你還要我保證\NI already swore to you, now you want me to promise, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.19,0:14:25.12,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我保證\NI promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.37,0:14:41.27,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}孩子 跟你說句話\NSon, a word with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.58,0:14:47.90,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}當船長 你不能當他們的朋友 你是他們的長官\NTo be a captain, you cannot be a friend, you are their superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.32,0:14:51.11,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}別忘了這點 讓別人記住這點\NNever forget that, never let THEM forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.05,0:14:53.35,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}謝謝\NThank you, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.55,0:14:57.45,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你的曾祖父和其他人創立了這個行業\NYour great-grandfather and a few others created this industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.65,0:15:02.02,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}沒有我們 沒有你們 世界將會陷入黑暗\NWithout us, without you, the world plunges into darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.22,0:15:05.23,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我希望能讓家族名譽生輝 先生\NI hope to bring honor to the Pollard family name, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.66,0:15:18.14,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}啊 上帝創造了巨大的鯨 體長無比的神奇怪物\NThou didst, O Lord, create the mighty whale, That wondrous monster of a mighty length;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.72,0:15:22.37,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}頭碩身龐尾又闊 無邊雄力人難度\NBeyond conception his unmeasured strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.57,0:15:28.39,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}恆古上帝宥永生 吾儕荏弱落凡塵\NBut, everlasting God, thou dost ordain that we, poor feeble mortals
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.45,0:15:33.50,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}妻兒一家須偷生\Nshould engage ourselves, our wives and children to maintain,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.55,0:15:38.13,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}賴此巨物維生存\NThis dreadful monster with a martial rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.71,0:15:46.36,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}啊 上帝 用您的榮耀之光照亮這些男人\NO Father, grant that your glorious light shine on these men,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.41,0:15:49.23,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}保佑他們豐收的航程\Nand assure them a prosperous voyage,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.28,0:15:53.11,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}保佑他們安全歸來\Nthat they may return SAFELY unto the womb ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.49,0:15:57.03,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}楠塔基特的白鯨油\NSo that the white whales of Nantucket whale oil
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.23,0:16:00.49,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}可以繼續照亮我們的房屋\Nmay continue to keep light in our homes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.69,0:16:07.15,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}照亮我們的街道 為工業機器提供燃料\Ncity streets safe from sin in the night, fuel the machines of industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.35,0:16:09.84,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}推動我們偉大的國家前進\Ndrive our great nation forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.04,0:16:16.44,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們文明種族進步 我們祈禱\Nas our noble species evolves. In Your name, we pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.21,0:16:28.25,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}現在是幾月\NSo, what month is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.45,0:16:32.01,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}年末了 我們是最後一批出海的船隻了\NOh, late in the year, we were one of the last ships to go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.38,0:16:35.51,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}也是為什麼我和我朋友巴爾齊萊有臥鋪\NWhich is why my friend Barzillai and I got a berth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.71,0:16:40.65,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}聽著 我當時14歲\NLook, I was fourteen... fourteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.66,0:16:44.42,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}尼克森 別站著 幹活\NNickerson, you're standin' around, boy! Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.52,0:16:48.07,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}第一次出海 很害怕 更害怕顯露出來\NFirst time at sea, scared, more scared to show it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.17,0:16:50.11,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}巴爾齊萊當時17歲\NBarzillai was seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.31,0:16:54.86,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}在碼頭長大的孤兒都等不及被別人視作大人\NOrphans, grew up on the wharf, both in a hurry to be called men.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.63,0:17:00.87,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你們慢騰騰幹嘛 裝船 快 快\NWhat are you all guys waiting for? Get it aboard! C'mon! Haul away...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.97,0:17:03.03,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他們戴的是飾針是什麼\NWhat are those pins they're wearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.08,0:17:04.39,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}那些是白鯨徽章 湯姆斯\NThose are whale pins, Thomas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.72,0:17:06.27,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我怎麼才能得到一個\NHow do I get one of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.32,0:17:09.05,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你得用長矛刺殺一頭白鯨\NWell, you've gotta thrust a killing lance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.25,0:17:11.75,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}那是世界上最大的怪物\NThe largest beast ever to breathe on the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.55,0:17:15.57,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}尼克森 把那綠色的東西給邦德先生\NNickerson, get the green stuff to Mr. Bond.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.44,0:17:18.18,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}快點 媽的\NMake it quick, damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.28,0:17:21.70,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我總有一天會有一堆那東西\NI shall have twelve of those one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.61,0:17:27.72,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}把它們放到匣子裏\NPut 'em on the Grandira casket.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.86,0:17:30.52,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你也上船就說明一件事\NWell, well, you being on board means only one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.57,0:17:34.50,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}是啊 這船上至少有一人明白歐文·查斯是誰\NYep! At least there's one person on this ship who knows the truth about Owen Chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.86,0:17:37.37,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}不 可惜其他的船都已經滿員了\NNo, but all the other ships have already crewed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.47,0:17:42.17,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}不不 我洗心革面了 歐文 問題是你呢\NNo, no, I'm a reformed man, Owen, the question is are YOU?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.27,0:17:44.59,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}別告訴我花花公子馬修戒酒了\NDon't tell me Matthew Joy has put down the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.71,0:17:48.20,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我有罪 歐文·查斯能消消他的壞脾氣了嗎\NI have sinned. Has Owen Chase put down his temper?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.40,0:17:50.09,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}平靜的像教堂\NSerene as the Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.29,0:17:52.33,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}照我看來\NI'll believe THAT when I see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.53,0:17:58.57,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}考慮到我們的船長 我覺得你只能平靜一小會兒\NGiven our captain I'll give your serenity about 48 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.48,0:18:00.81,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}祝你好運\NGood luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.66,0:18:10.39,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}波拉德 喬治·波拉德 歐文·查斯\N- Pollard, George Pollard. - Owen Chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.59,0:18:15.15,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}查斯 你父親的名字對嗎 對 是的\N- Chase, your father's name, isn't it? - Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.35,0:18:19.97,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}馬上他要離開島一段時間而我舒適得待在家\NVery shortly he will be off island for some time and I'll be very much at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.78,0:18:26.36,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我要說 我有點意外 通常船長可以選擇自己的大副\NI say, I was surprised, normally a captain gets to choose his first mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.56,0:18:28.78,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}如果是有經驗的船長的話 是的\NAn experienced captain, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.98,0:18:30.87,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}當人 你可以理解老頭的意思\NOf course, you can understand from the owners' point of view,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.98,0:18:33.42,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他們想讓自己的財產在適合的人手裏\Nthey wanted to put their investments in the hands of men.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.13,0:18:34.92,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}確實\NIndeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.02,0:18:37.96,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他們也許想要多些保障\NThey probably wanted a little extra reassurance, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.16,0:18:41.05,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}看著點我 如果我做錯什麼了告訴我\NWell, DO keep an eye on me, let me know if I'm doing anything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.19,0:18:43.38,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我不會遲疑的 船長\NI'd have it not other way, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.59,0:18:56.36,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}起錨\NShore up the anchor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.40,0:18:58.60,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}起風了 頂部橫桿放下了嗎 好\N- Head's in the wind, is the top rail off? - Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.72,0:19:00.01,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}克拉德 掌舵 好\N- Collard, Take the helm! - Aye!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.13,0:19:01.19,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}花花公子 揚帆\NMr. Joy, make sail.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.29,0:19:03.87,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}科爾 查普爾 守在起錨器旁\NMr. Cole, Mr. Chappel, stand by this anchor!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.73,0:19:26.83,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}查普爾 掌舵\NMr. Chappel, take the helm!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.80,0:19:32.02,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}為什麼帆布還沒有鬆開\NBoyd! Why aren't those braces laid out?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.51,0:19:48.26,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}打開帆 媽的\NSet the sail, god damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.31,0:19:57.06,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}跑開\NHeading to scram.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.16,0:20:00.13,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}船長 注意頭上 後面 船長\N- Captain! Heads up! - Behind you head, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.06,0:20:06.45,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}怎麼了 謝潑德 帆布纏住了 長官\N- What happened, Mr. Sheppard? - The jalousie felled the sheet, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.33,0:20:11.36,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}帆布纏住了 查斯 他辦不到\N- The jalousie's jammed! - Chase, she still won't clear!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.06,0:20:23.86,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}當心\NWatch your step!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.06,0:20:26.17,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}帆布 歐文\NIt's the jalousie, Owen!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.51,0:20:38.95,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}走開\NStand clear!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.02,0:21:08.22,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}幹的漂亮 查斯\NNice piece of work, Mr. Chase!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.61,0:21:22.57,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}如果兩周內能到佛得角\NIf we make Cape Verdes in the next 2 weeks we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.62,0:21:25.93,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們有很大幾率能按時到太平洋\Nhave a decent chance of reaching the Pacific on schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.48,0:21:30.44,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}玉米棒 查斯\NCorn, Mr. Chase?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.59,0:21:33.74,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}不需要 謝謝 從來不喜歡\NNo, thank you, Sir, never did have much of a taste for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:36.02,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}太怪了\NThat's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.52,0:21:40.53,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你爸在科德角是種玉米的吧 是的\N- So, your father grew corn on Cape Cod. - That's right, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.73,0:21:43.92,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你也猜到了 我那時天天吃這個吃膩了\NAs you can imagine, I suddenly grew tired of eating it every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.31,0:21:52.14,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}種玉米 秋葵 大豆 然後他進了監獄\NCorn, okra, beans, I believe? Before he went to jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.66,0:21:57.37,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}花花公子 聽起來熟悉嗎\NAre you familiar with this story, Mr. Joy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.11,0:22:04.60,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你知道查斯是因為他的父親進監獄才變成孤兒的嗎\NWere you aware that Mr. Chase was effectively orphaned due to his father's incarceration?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.75,0:22:08.14,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們都有不同的經歷\NWell, we all have our paths to sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.63,0:22:11.73,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}所以還是不要問太多問題為好\NThat's a motive to not ask too many questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.12,0:22:15.64,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}一定不容易吧\NCan't have been easy though, yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.35,0:22:20.07,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}楠塔基特最偉大的航海家族收留你\NYou had Nantucket's great seafaring family to adopt you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.27,0:22:23.81,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}很久沒有楠塔基特人稱呼我陸人\NThis is far from the first time I've been called a landsman...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.91,0:22:29.98,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}或者提醒我不是他們一家人了\Nor off-islander by some Nantucket reminding me how I am NOT part of their family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.70,0:22:35.56,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}請允許我 船長 我要去分配捕鯨船和值班了\NNow, if the captain will excuse me, there are whale boats and watches to assign.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.99,0:22:45.25,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}不 船長 滴酒不沾\N- No, Sir, not for me. - Not a drop?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.35,0:22:51.01,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}不 船長 就像我說的 有時候少問問題更好\NNo, Sir, like I said, sometimes the fewer questions one asks, the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.46,0:23:12.29,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}花花公子 這有個漂亮姑娘\NThat's a gorgeous girl, Mr. Joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.34,0:23:16.16,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}遠東的鯨骨上刻的\NRegion of move me that, carved from a Far East whalebone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.36,0:23:18.52,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}不許碰\NNo touching!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.72,0:23:19.82,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我一直以為你已經結婚了\NI always thought you were married anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.93,0:23:22.18,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}是的 但看她\NI am, and there she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.38,0:23:25.09,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}這是她的鼻子\NWell, that's her nose anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.97,0:23:27.75,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}恭喜 女士們\NCongratulations, ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.07,0:23:32.70,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}今天啟航幹的不錯\NThat was a fine job trimin' sails today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.90,0:23:36.66,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我從來沒有過這麼一群捕鯨人\NA sorrier pack of deck-whalers I don't think I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.15,0:23:40.37,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}查普爾 長官\N- Mr. Chappel. - Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.57,0:23:42.16,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}船長魚叉手\NCaptain's harpooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.36,0:23:45.75,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}勞倫斯 你做我的 遵命 長官\N- Mr. Lawrence, you'll be mine. - Aye, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.95,0:23:50.61,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}彼得森 二副的魚叉手\NAnd Mr. Peterson, second mate's harpooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.81,0:23:51.51,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}遵命 長官\NAye, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.61,0:23:56.10,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}一船上六人 首要一點要警覺\NThere'll be six men to a boat, first rules in the row, six bells sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.20,0:23:59.23,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們還沒到哈利法克斯以東 長官\NWe're not even east of Halifax, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.43,0:24:03.34,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你叫什麼 克芬 亨利·克芬\N- What's your name? - Coffin, Henry Coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.54,0:24:05.61,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}他是船長的表弟 長官\NHe's the Captain's cousin, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.93,0:24:11.75,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}克芬先生 你覺得一頭白鯨會知道自己在哈利法克斯以東嗎\NWell, well, Mr. Coffin, do you think a whale knows it's east of Halifax?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.71,0:24:18.49,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我不知道你們原來是誰 或者怎麼來的\NI don't know who all of you are, or how you got here,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.69,0:24:21.67,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你們中一些人可能甚至是重犯 在隱藏或者逃亡\NSome of you probably have felonies, or are hidin' or on the run.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.82,0:24:26.81,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}沒關係 我不關心 我對你們的要求只有一個\NThat's fine, I don't give a damn, but we interred you for just one thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.02,0:24:31.47,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}只有一個 就是鯨油\Nand one thing only, and that is whale oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.67,0:24:35.58,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我要裝滿2000桶油並盡快回家\NI intend to fill our 2000 barrels and be home as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.79,0:24:39.38,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}即使天氣好而且沒有鯨出沒 克芬先生\NAnd even when the weather is fine and there ARE no whales, Mr. Coffin,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.43,0:24:44.09,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我們會放下船練習如何捕鯨\Nwe will lower the boats and practice all maneuvers necessary in a capture of a whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.19,0:24:47.55,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}誰要是想偷懶就自己游回家 明白嗎\NAnd any man who is idle will find himself swimmin' to home. Is that understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.73,0:24:49.94,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}明白 長官\N- Aye, sir. Aye, Sir. - Aye, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.59,0:24:57.16,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}小子 上甲板\NGreen horn, on deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.01,0:25:01.83,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}走\NOn ya go!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.11,0:25:06.48,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}遵命 遵命 陸人\NAye, aye, landsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.58,0:25:09.02,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}湯姆·尼克森 對吧 是的 長官\N- Thomas Nickerson, right? - Aye, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.22,0:25:11.60,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}有些人一開始會覺得噁心\NYa know, some feel sick at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.59,0:25:18.94,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}拉我上去 這是最好的辦法\N- Pull me back up! - Best way to square up to King Neptune, Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.13,0:25:20.62,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}求你了 拉我上去\NPlease, bring me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.94,0:25:26.90,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}好點了嗎\NBetter now?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.11,0:25:33.49,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}長官 非常對不起\NSir, I am so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.52,0:25:37.80,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}你現在有故事寫信回家告訴你母親了\NWell, now you got something to write home to your mother about.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.33,0:25:44.99,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我母親葬在史密斯山\NMy mother's buried up in Smith's Hill,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.19,0:25:47.57,中文,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(97,280)\fscx50\fscy100}我爸也是 他\Nand a stone for my father, too, he was...
